---
import SolidButton from '../../components/actions/buttons/SolidButton.astro';
import OutlineButton from '../../components/actions/buttons/OutlineButton.astro';
import SectionHeading from '../../components/typography/SectionHeading.astro';
import RadioSmallCard from '../../components/inputs/RadioSmallCard.astro';

const textClasses =
  'text-sm/6 sm:text-base/7 md:text-lg/8 m-0 font-light text-left sm:text-justify';

const tiers = [
  { amount: 5, link: 'https://donate.stripe.com/00w9AS8dt8UC1ox31jfQI01' },
  { amount: 10, link: 'https://donate.stripe.com/5kQaEWfFV8UC7MV45nfQI02' },
  { amount: 25, link: 'https://donate.stripe.com/eVq4gyfFV3Ai8QZ6dvfQI03' },
];

const defaultTier = tiers[1];
---

<div id="why-support" class="flex flex-col gap-10">
  <div class="flex flex-col gap-4 md:gap-8">
    <SectionHeading text="Why Support" classes="text-center" />
    <div class="flex flex-col gap-4">
      <p class={textClasses}>
        Our experience in the digital world is more and more enshittified,
        characterized by ubiquitous surveillance, paywalls and advertising. <em
          >v2</em
        > is
        <a
          href="https://oktana.dev"
          class="text-purple-500"
          target="_blank"
          rel="noopener">our</a
        > first attempt to reverse this trend: it doesn't track your behavior or
        try to lock you in. It's a tool that is meant to enhance your capacity for
        thinking, creating knowledge and collaborating without distractions. It is
        also interoperable, trying to be a part of your creative workflow and not
        monopolize it. Its source code is open, which makes it part of a global knowledge
        commons that is revolutionizing the way we produce and collaborate using
        digital media.
      </p>
      <p class={textClasses}>
        But all the above make <em>v2</em> resistant to becoming a <em
          >commodity</em
        >, which is something expected and desirable for us: we aim to
        decommodify knowledge production and social life as much as possible.
        This makes it <strong>really hard</strong> for the project to be sustainable
        economically without a continuous support from our user community. Quality
        software is expensive to build and maintain: designing an intuitive user
        experience, implementing features, fixing bugs, responding to issues, keeping
        up with operating system changes, improving performance. Also, the reality
        is that <em>v2</em> competes with big-tech alternatives leveraging infinitely
        more resources, worker exploitation and ecosystem lock-in.
      </p>
      <p class={textClasses}>
        Your support is the best way to ensure that <em>v2</em> stays well-maintained,
        independent and open.
      </p>
    </div>
    <div class="flex flex-col justify-center items-center gap-4">
      <h2
        class="text-lg md:text-xl text-black/85 dark:text-white/85 font-serif font-bold text-center"
      >
        Choose how you'd like to contribute
      </h2>
      <div class="flex flex-col justify-center gap-4 w-full sm:max-w-sm">
        <p class="text-xs/6 text-black/54 text-center">
          Steady funding keeps v2 independent and sustainable.
        </p>

        <fieldset>
          <legend class="sr-only">Monthly support amount</legend>
          <div class="tier-picker grid grid-cols-3 gap-3">
            <!--
              The checked property just sets the default. The Tailwind has-checked:
              variant uses the CSS :checked pseudo-class under the hood,
              which tracks the DOM property, not the HTML attribute.
            -->
            {
              tiers.map((tier) => (
                <RadioSmallCard
                  value={tier.link}
                  label={`€${tier.amount}/month`}
                  group="support-tier"
                  checked={tier.link === defaultTier.link}
                />
              ))
            }
          </div>
        </fieldset>

        <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row sm:justify-between gap-4">
          <a
            id="recurring-support-link"
            href={defaultTier.link}
            target="_blank"
            rel="noopener"
            class="flex-auto"
          >
            <SolidButton
              icon="fa-stripe"
              text="Become a monthly supporter"
              subtitle="From €5/mo – cancel anytime"
              size="lg"
              classes="w-full"
            />
          </a>
        </div>

        <div class="flex flex-col gap-4">
          <p class="text-xs/6 text-black/54 text-center">
            Other ways to contribute
          </p>
          <div class="flex flex-col gap-4">
            <a
              href="https://donate.stripe.com/6oU5kC51hfj03wF7hzfQI00"
              target="_blank"
              rel="noopener"
              class="flex-auto"
            >
              <OutlineButton
                icon="fa-stripe"
                text="One-time contribution"
                size="sm"
                classes="w-full"
              />
            </a>
            <a
              href="https://opencollective.com/oktana"
              target="_blank"
              rel="noopener"
              class="flex-auto"
            >
              <OutlineButton
                icon="open-collective"
                text="Open Collective"
                size="sm"
                classes="w-full"
              />
            </a>
            <a
              href="https://github.com/sponsors/oktana-coop"
              target="_blank"
              rel="noopener"
              class="flex-auto"
            >
              <OutlineButton
                icon="fa-github"
                text="GitHub Sponsors"
                size="sm"
                classes="w-full"
              />
            </a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<script>
  const radios = document.querySelectorAll<HTMLInputElement>(
    '.tier-picker input[type="radio"]'
  );
  const recurringSupportLink = document.getElementById(
    'recurring-support-link'
  ) as HTMLAnchorElement | null;

  if (recurringSupportLink) {
    radios.forEach((radio) => {
      radio.addEventListener('change', () => {
        recurringSupportLink.href = radio.value;
      });
    });
  }
</script>
